        <Label x:Name="Subtitle" Content="else statement" HorizontalAlignment="Left" VerticalAlignment="Top" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="20" Margin="-1,-2,0,0" FontWeight="Bold"/>
        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="6,26,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="420" Grid.RowSpan="2"><Run Text="So what happens if the condition inside your if statement is false? If the result is false, the action statements inside the if won't be executed. Maybe you want something else to happen if your condition isn't met. &quot;If&quot; not this, then do something &quot;else&quot;."/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The else statement is an optional part of the if statement, but it can't be alone. It must come with use of the if statement. "/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>

